&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;At the summit I spoke briefly with Boanerges about cleric AC mitigation and the AC cap. The AC cap for clerics is higher than other priest classes, and at the time I also claimed that the return for AC over the cap was better for clerics over other priest classes. Looking over the data, I found this to be not true – currently clerics receive the same returns from AC over the cap as other priests.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;After evaluating this today, we’ve decided to go ahead and increase the AC over the cap for clerics to match that of bards – so that bards and clerics will have both the same AC cap and same returns from AC over the cap, making their gains from AC be equal.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;As far as bards are concerned, I also looked over the AC cap values for their class. Currently, the AC value for bards is set to the same values as that of monks and rogues. This seems to also be too low and after evaluation, bards will have the same cap as clerics, which is a higher value.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt?&gt;These two changes should give both clerics and bards more gains from AC from gear than before.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Zajeer-Dev on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;10-05-2005&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;06:40 PM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
